## Create database

```bash
sudo -iu postgres
createdb ebackend
```

## Prepare

```bash
cp config.yaml.example config.yaml
```

And then edit `config.yaml` file.

## Run HTTP-server

```bash
make run
```

## Building

Build binary:

```bash
make build
```

Clean:

```bash
make clean
```

Run binary:

```bash
./build/{{ .PkgName }} serve
```
## Run with docker

Build image:

```bash
docker build -f Dockerfile -t {{ .PkgName }} .
```

Run:

```bash
docker run --name {{ .PkgName }} --rm --network host \
-v "$(pwd)/config.yaml:/app/config.yaml" \
{{ .PkgName }}
```

